      <p>We are the team behind Podsmack. A user friendly web application focused around assisting in finding your next favorite podcast.</p>
      <p>The goal of this project was to create a successful Rails application from an idea to delivery within a weeks time, focused around solving a problem. The podcast world is full of options, so how do you narrow down the search based on your interests? What we have created authenticates through a third-party service (Google), and consumes an api (Listen Notes) to find podcasts based around selecting location, custom tags, content rating, or searching through name.</p>
      <p> We used an agile process developing our features. Also, Configured a continuous integration server, caching, and implemented a Sinatra Microservice. The tech stack used for this project are the following:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Ruby on Rails</li>
          <li>Active Record</li>
          <li>Sinatra</li>
          <li>Travis CI</li>
